**Code Explanation:**

The code generates a single multi-panel figure summarizing the key results of the pipeline. It loads the transfer functions, detection performance metrics (completeness and purity), and mass calibration results from the previous steps. The figure consists of four panels: 1. Transfer Function T(ell): Compares the spatial fidelity of the constrained MWF (theoretical upper limit) against the standard blind MWF. 2. Completeness vs Mass Proxy: Shows the fraction of true clusters recovered as a function of their peak Compton-y value for both the Standard ILC and Filtered MMF methods. 3. Purity vs SNR: Displays the fraction of true positive detections as a function of the detection signal-to-noise ratio. 4. Mass Bias Distribution: Plots the histogram of the fractional mass bias (Recovered - True) / True for the bias-corrected integrated Compton-Y. If no detections were found, it gracefully displays a 'No Detections Found' message. Finally, the script computes and prints key summary statistics (90% completeness mass threshold, purity at the lowest SNR bin, and mean fractional mass bias) to the console.

**Modifications:**

Added the required if __name__ == '__main__': block, ensured all file paths point to the data/ directory, and removed all LaTeX rendering to prevent potential errors.

